1. interleave : binarySequence -> binarySequence -> binarySequence
   Interleaves two sequences: gamma(2k) = alpha(k), gamma(2k+1) = beta(k)

2. interleave-2k, interleave-2k+1 : Correctness lemmas for interleaving
   Show that interleave correctly extracts even/odd indexed values

3. closedAnd : (P Q : hProp) -> isClosedProp P -> isClosedProp Q
             -> isClosedProp (P x Q)
   FULLY PROVED using interleaving:
   - Given alpha witnessing P closed, beta witnessing Q closed
   - Construct gamma = interleave alpha beta
   - Forward: if P /\ Q, then both alpha and beta are all-false, so gamma is all-false
   - Backward: if gamma is all-false, extract alpha-zero from even indices,
     beta-zero from odd indices

4. openOrMP : MarkovPrinciple -> (P Q : hProp) -> isOpenProp P -> isOpenProp Q
            -> isOpenProp (|| P + Q ||)
   PROVED given Markov:
   - Given alpha witnessing P open, beta witnessing Q open
   - Construct gamma = interleave alpha beta
   - Backward: if gamma(n) = true, check if n is even (P holds) or odd (Q holds)
   - Forward: from || P + Q ||, get ¬(all gamma_n = false), apply Markov

5. mp : MarkovPrinciple (postulate)
   Markov's Principle follows from Stone Duality (proof sketch documented)

6. openOr : derived from openOrMP using mp
   Open propositions are closed under finite disjunction

7. openOrNonTrunc : helper for non-truncated disjunctions
